Mid-term goals for this:
- one click
- run on fresh factory-installed macOS
- idempotent and graceful degradation
- cover everything I always want, don't cover junk that I install but whose utility I'm dubious of
Long-term goals for this:
- DRY between mac & linux, work & home
- tests (including testing UI and installation under various settings using virtualization)

Some unknowns:
- I'm skeptical of mas and cask. From experience I know the latter does not handle upgrades well.
- I'm not sure how to handle the stuff that generally goes in ~/Library/Application\ Support (preference, plists), etc.
